<div id="form-description">
    <p>GEO2Enrichr is a web application for extracting gene sets from SOFT files and analyzing these lists for common biological functions. Choose between two methods of gene set extraction:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Install the <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/geo2enrichr/pcbdeobileclecleblcnadplfcicfjlp">Chrome Extension</a> to use GEO2Enrichr on the <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/" target="_blank">Gene Expression Omnbius</a> website.</li>
        <li>Use the form below to upload a SOFT file. Please see our <a href="#help">Help Page</a> for details on file formatting.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Click <a href="#example">here</a> to use an example SOFT file to see the application's output.</p>
</div>
